data.name: MOCOM Compounds
data.description:
MOCOM is a global compounder of thermoplastic polymers. The company with its headquarter in Hamburg, Germany, offers the plastics processing industry a comprehensive range of high-performance customized and standard compound solutions. The high performance and engineering compounds are complimented by the recyclate based compounds which deliver Near-To-Prime properties. MOCOM supplies a wide range of industries including Automotive, Electrical and Electronics, Home and Garden, Sports and Leisure, Transportation, and Healthcare.


As part of the Otto Krahn Group, MOCOM currently employs around 800 people. It has production sites in Duncan, South Carolina (USA), three German locations (Hamburg, Erlenbach, Zülpich) as well as in Changshu (China).



For more information visit mocom.eu/en

data.name: ALTECH® ECO PC 2030/200 GF30
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALTECH® ECO PC 2030/200 GF30 is a polycarbonate base polymer containing 30% glass fibers and recycled material, suitable for applications such as plugs/connectors, housings, and other household goods and energy management. To ensure optimal performance, pre-drying conditions require a dry air (dessiccant) dryer at 100-120°C for 2-3 h, or an air circulating dryer at 100-120°C for 4-12 h depending on moisture content, with a maximum moisture content of <0.02%.

data.name: ALTECH® ECO PC 1000/141 FR
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALTECH® ECO PC 1000/141 FR is a polycarbonate base polymer with special features such as UV stabilization, easy release (demolding), and flame retardant impact modification. It is suitable for pre-drying conditions in an air circulating dryer at 100-120°C for 4-12 hours, or 120°C in a dry air (dessiccant) dryer for 2-3 hours, dependent on the moisture content with a maximum moisture content of 0.02%. It can be used for applications in the electrical and electronic, lighting, and various markets such as housings, security engineering parts, sockets, plugs/connectors, and various others.

data.name: ALFATER® XL A60I 4GP0000
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALFATER® XL A60I 4GP0000 is a thermoplastic vulcanisate (PP+EPDM) with a natural color and bright inherent color. It is suitable for automotive, building and construction, electrical and electronic, sport and leisure and furniture applications, and is suitable for injection molded parts, seals, sealing lips, handles, racking/shelving, soft touch elements, impact protection/shock absorbers, protection caps, thin walled parts, profiles, cable ducts, casters, and 2K components. It has good adhesion to polypropylene homopolymer, polypropylene copolymer, polyethylene, thermoplastic vulcanisate (PP+EPDM), thermoplastic olefin elastomer, thermoplastic elastomer general, and ethylene propylene diene rubber. It is resistant to heat, weather and ozone.

data.name: ALTECH® PP-H A 3030/100
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALTECH® PP-H A 3030/100 is a polypropylene homopolymer with a 30% glass bead filler/additive system, specially designed for easy release (demolding) and slip agent. It is suitable for injection molding with a melt temperature of 200-250°C and a mold temperature of 20-70°C and can be used to create building and construction, sport and leisure applications, such as injection molded parts, interior and household goods, hygiene products, and housings. To ensure best results, pre-drying conditions should be in an air circulating dryer at 80-120°C for 2-4 h, or in a dry air (dessiccant) dryer at 80-120°C for 2-3 h.

data.name: ALFATER® XL A85E 2GP0000
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALFATER® XL A85E 2GP0000 is a Thermoplastic Vulcanisate (PP+EPDM) with natural color, black color, and high viscosity. It has good weathering resistance, good chemical resistance, good ozone resistance, good hot air resistance, and good hydrolysis resistance. It is used in the Automotive, building and construction, Machinery, electrical and electronic, and Furniture industries for extruded parts, blow molded parts, and coextrusion. It can be used for profile, seals, sealing lip, conduit, tubes, cable guides, cable jacketing, bellows, and air duct, as well as 2K components. Its adhesion to Polypropylene Homopolymer, Polypropylene Copolymer, polyethylene, Thermoplastic Vulcanisate (PP+EPDM), Thermoplastic Olefin Elastomer, and Thermoplastic Elastomer has been tested generally.

data.name: ALTECH® ABS A 1000/206
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALTECH® ABS A 1000/206 is a base polymer acrylonitrile/butadiene/styrene/copolymer used in various market segments for injection molded parts. For pre-drying, conditions should be 80°C in an air circulating dryer for 3-6 hours and 80°C in a dry air (dessiccant) dryer for 2-4 hours, depending on moisture content, with a maximum moisture content of less than 0.20%. For processing, injection molding requires a melt temperature of 200-240°C and a mold temperature of 50-80°C.

data.name: ALFATER® XL A55I 2GP0050
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALFATER® XL A55I 2GP0050 is a black thermoplastic vulcanisate (PP+EPDM) suitable for pre-drying conditions in a dry air (dessiccant) dryer with temperatures of 70-80°C for 2-4 hours with a maximum moisture content of <0.10%. It has good recovery, weathering resistance, chemical resistance, ozone resistance, hot air resistance, and hydrolysis resistance. It is used mainly in the injection molding process with melt temperatures of 195-230°C, mold temperatures of 10-60°C, high injection speed, and back pressure (hydraulic) >5 bar and holding pressure 50-70% of injection pressure. It is used in automotive, building and construction, electrical and electronic, machinery, and furniture applications for injection molded parts such as seals, sealing lips, handles, soft touch elements, impact protection/shock absorbers, protection caps, cable ducts, plugs, fasteners, and connectors, 2K components.

data.name: TEDUR® L PPS 1000 15087
data.description: MOCOM Compounds TEDUR® L PPS 1000 15087 is a polyphenylene sulfide base polymer that has been elastomer modified for high toughness. It is suitable for both extrusion and injection molding. The pre-drying conditions should be in a dry air (dessiccant) dryer at 100-130°C for 2-4 hours. The melt temperature for extrusion should be 290-310°C, while the melt temperature and mold temperature for injection molding should be 290-310°C and >100°C respectively. This product is typically used for ducting/piping systems and functional components in the automotive and machinery market segments, providing superior toughness and performance.

data.name: ALTECH® PP-H A 4920/170 MR20
data.description: MOCOM Compounds ALTECH® PP-H A 4920/170 MR20 is a Polypropylene Homopolymer with a 20% talcum filler/additive system. It is designed for pre-drying conditions in a dry air (dessiccant) dryer at 80-120°C for 2-3 hours, or in an air circulating dryer at 80-120°C for 2-4 hours. For injection molding, the melt temperature should be 200-250°C and the mold temperature should be 20-70°C. It has easy release (demolding) and processing and heat stabilization features. This material is suitable for automotive, building and construction applications, and can be used for injection molded parts, functional components, housings and fixing elements.

data.name: WIC PA6 10 BK
data.description: WIC PA6 10 BK is a polyamide 6 base polymer filled with 10% carbon fiber and colored black. It has medium viscosity and heat aging stabilization, and is designed for automotive and sport markets. To ensure optimal performance, pre-drying conditions should be 80°C in a dry-air dryer for 2-8h, depending on moisture content, with a maximum moisture content of 0.12%. Processing conditions for injection molding include melt temperatures of 250-270°C and mold temperatures of 60-100°C. Additionally, the increased thermal conductivity should be taken into account under certain conditions.

data.name: WIC PA6 10 N
data.description: WIC PA6 10 N is a polyamide 6 base polymer with 10% carbon fiber filler, in a natural (carbon optic) color. It has medium viscosity and is heat aging stabilized. For optimal results, it should be pre-dried at 80°C in a dry-air dryer for 2-8 hours, depending on moisture content, with a maximum moisture content of 0.12%. Processing conditions require injection molding with a melt temperature of 250-270°C and a mold temperature of 60-100°C. This material is suitable for the automotive and sport market segments. It should be noted that under certain conditions, increased thermal conductivity should be taken into account.

data.name: WIC PA66 30 BK EF
data.description: WIC PA66 30 BK EF is a polyamide 66 base polymer with 30% carbon fiber filler and black color, specially designed for easy flow and heat aging stabilization. It is mainly used in the automotive and sport market segments. Processing conditions include injection molding with a melt temperature of 280-300°C and a mold temperature of 80-120°C. Under certain conditions, increased thermal conductivity must be considered. To ensure optimal performance, it should be stored in a dry, light-protected environment.

data.name: WIC PA66 30 N
data.description: WIC PA66 30 N is a polyamide 66 base polymer filled with 30% carbon fiber and colored natural (carbon optic). It has medium viscosity and is heat aging stabilized, making it suitable for use in automotive and sport market segments. Pre-drying conditions for this product involve 80°C in a dry-air dryer for 2-8h, depending on the moisture content.

data.name: WIC PA66 40 BK
data.description: WIC PA66 40 BK is a polyamide 66 base polymer filled with 40% carbon fiber and black in color. It has medium viscosity, heat aging stabilization, and is suitable for automotive and sport market segments. data.name: WIC PA66 40 N

data.name: MOCOM Compounds
data.description:
MOCOM is a global compounder of thermoplastic polymers. The company with its headquarter in Hamburg, Germany, offers the plastics processing industry a comprehensive range of high-performance customized and standard compound solutions. The high performance and engineering compounds are complimented by the recyclate based compounds which deliver Near-To-Prime properties. MOCOM supplies a wide range of industries including Automotive, Electrical and Electronics, Home and Garden, Sports and Leisure, Transportation, and Healthcare.


As part of the Otto Krahn Group, MOCOM currently employs around 800 people. It has production sites in Duncan, South Carolina (USA), three German locations (Hamburg, Erlenbach, Zülpich) as well as in Changshu (China).



For more information visit mocom.eu/en
